org.openbel.framework.common.model
Class Document

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.common.model.Document
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<Statement>, BELModelObject
public class Document
extends Object
implements BELModelObject, Iterable<Statement>

BEL documents are structured text documents which contain BEL statements along with sufficient additional information to fully describe and process the document.

BEL documents contain a number of statements organized into statement groups. Documents are statement-iterable: 

 
 for (final Statement statement : document) {
     // ...
 }

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

mapStatements

public Map<StatementGroup,Set<Statement>> mapStatements()
Returns a map of statement group to a set of statements.

The returned map is not backed by the document. If the document is modified in any way, the returned map may no longer reflect a correct mapping of statement group to statement set.

Returns:
Map of StatementGroup to Set of Statements

iterator

public Iterator<Statement> iterator()
Returns an iterator over the document's statements.

The following code is guaranteed to be safe (no null pointer exceptions will be thrown): 

 
 for (final Statement statement : document) {
 }
